description:
This software is developed to perform backup, restore and synchronization of data under 2000/XP/2003/Vista operating systems.


Main features of Handy Backup
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

- Support full, incremental and mirror backup;
- Image Backup - backup of entire hard drive contents, including operating system, registry, drivers, programs and data files.
- Synchronize files and folders between servers, desktops, notebooks, LANs, ZIP disks, secondary hard disks, etc.
- Support for different types of backup storage including FTP/SFTP, removable media and all types of LANS;
- Full CD/DVD/Blu-Ray/HD-DVD support with disk spanning enabling user to divide a large backup set into parts saved onto several disks;
- Speed selection for CD/DVD/Blu-Ray/HD-DVD;
- Integrated ZIP compression; 
- 128 bit encryption support for stored data; 
- Flexible and powerful scheduler; 
- Can run the application as a service on Windows 2000/XP/2003/Vista systems;
- Fast backup of ODBC compatible databases such as MySQL, DB2, MS Access, MSSQL, Oracle and other;
- Backup of MS Exchange Server including mail, contacts, calendar and tasks
- Easy backup of Lotus Notes/Domino databases. v. 6.5 and higher;
- Special plug-ins to backup data from different applications such as Outlook, The Bat Pro, ICQ, AOL and Yahoo! Instant Messengers, FireFox, Adobe Photoshop;
- Allows backing up an e-mail box contents directly from the email server.
- Can back up Windows registry and Windows settings: Favorites, Desktop, etc.
- E-mail notifications about operation results;
- Command line interface for professional users;
- Multi-threaded transfer engine that executes backups in the background with minimum system resource consumption; 
- Backup of several folders or files at a time;
- Option to run backup on log on/log off; 
- Option to set other programs to run before/after running a backup task;
- Flexible file/folder selection and file masks (filters) handling; 
- Import/export of all settings and registration status; 
- Improved timestamp settings;
- Drag&amp;Drop from Windows Explorer;
- Tray icon displays status of current operation;
- Online Backup Feature added.


